sentences.en: All the cupboards and appliances dated from the 1950s.
sentences.cn: 所有这些橱柜和家用电器都是20世纪50年代的物品。

sentences.en: All three structures dated to the third century and were tentatively identified as shrines.
sentences.cn: 这3座建筑都建于3世纪,并且初步鉴定为神庙.

sentences.en: Archaeologists have dated the fort to the reign of Emperor Antoninus Pius.
sentences.cn: 考古学家判定这个堡垒建于罗马皇帝安东尼·庇护统治时期。

sentences.en: Irving Kristol delivered the coup de grace in a letter dated June 12: they had decided to reject the proposal.
sentences.cn: 欧文·克里斯托尔在6月12日的一封信中发出了最后一击：他们已经决定驳回该提议。

sentences.en: Mike dated in his mind whether to accept the work.
sentences.cn: 迈克在心中考虑着是否接受这项工作.

sentences.en: She deserted her boyfriend she had dated for two years.
sentences.cn: 她把好了两年的对象给甩了.

sentences.en: She used rather dated words and phrases.
sentences.cn: 她使用的词语未免太陈旧了.

sentences.en: That dress looks a bit dated now.
sentences.cn: 那件连衣裙现在看起来有点过时了。

sentences.en: The Clark boy. Quarterback on the Winterset team. Dated Judy Leverenson.
sentences.cn: 那是克拉克家孩子的车, 他是温特塞特橄榄球队的四分卫,跟裘迪. 莱弗伦森经常约会.

sentences.en: The French Foreign Legion was founded by a Royal Ordinance, written on a small piece of official Prench War Office notepaper dated March 9 th, 1931.
sentences.cn: 法国外籍兵团是按照皇家的一项法令建立的, 这项法令记录在一小页法国陆军部公函信笺上, 日期是1931年3月9日.
备忘录上注明的日期是2008年8月23日.

sentences.en: The statue has been dated as 5 th century BC.
sentences.cn: 这个雕像的年代为公元前5世纪.

sentences.en: This album has hardly dated at all.
sentences.cn: 这张专辑几乎一点都不过时。
